<major-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/lordswms/2004-10-14a.25.0" nospeaker="true" colnum="25"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200304/ldhansrd/vo041014/text/41014-38.htm#41014-38_head1">
	House of Lords: Recess Dates
</major-heading>

<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/lordswms/2004-10-14a.25.1" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100264" speakername="Lord Grocott" colon=":" colnum="25"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200304/ldhansrd/vo041014/text/41014-38.htm#41014-38_spnew4">
	<p pid="a.25.1/1">At Commons Business Questions today, my right honourable friend Peter Hain MP announced the following provisional recess dates for the House of Commons:</p>
	<p pid="a.25.1/2" class="italic">Christmas</p>
	<p pid="a.25.1/3">Rise close of play&mdash;<phrase class="date" code="">Tuesday 21 December</phrase> Return&mdash;<phrase class="date" code="2006-01-10">Monday 10 January</phrase></p>
	<p pid="a.25.1/4" class="italic">Constituency week</p>
	<p pid="a.25.1/5">Rise close of play&mdash;<phrase class="date" code="2006-02-10">Thursday 10 February</phrase> Return&mdash;<phrase class="date" code="2006-02-21">Monday 21 February</phrase></p>
	<p pid="a.25.1/6" class="italic">Easter</p>
	<p pid="a.25.1/7">Rise close of play&mdash;<phrase class="date" code="2006-03-24">Thursday 24 March</phrase> Return&mdash;<phrase class="date" code="">Monday 4 April</phrase></p>
	<p pid="a.25.1/8" class="italic">Whitsun</p>
	<p pid="a.25.1/9">Rise close of play&mdash;<phrase class="date" code="">Thursday 26 May</phrase> Return&mdash;<phrase class="date" code="">Monday 6 June</phrase></p>
	<p pid="a.25.1/10" class="italic">Summer</p>
	<p pid="a.25.1/11">Rise close of play&mdash;<phrase class="date" code="">Thursday 28 July</phrase> Return&mdash;<phrase class="date" code="">Monday 10 October</phrase></p>
	<p pid="a.25.1/12">It is my intention to match these dates for the House of Lords, subject of course to the requirements and progress of business.</p>
	<p pid="a.25.1/13">It is not proposed to have a September sitting next year, because work needs to be done in the Commons Chamber.</p>
</speech>

<minor-heading id="uk.org.publicwhip/lordswms/2004-10-14a.25.2" nospeaker="true" colnum="25"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200304/ldhansrd/vo041014/text/41014-38.htm#41014-38_spmin0">
	Firearms Consultative Committee Report
</minor-heading>

<speech id="uk.org.publicwhip/lordswms/2004-10-14a.25.3" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100574" speakername="Baroness Scotland of Asthal" colon=":" colnum="25"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld200304/ldhansrd/vo041014/text/41014-38.htm#41014-38_spmin1">
	<p pid="a.25.3/1">We have today laid before Parliament the 12th annual report of the Firearms Consultative Committee, copies of which have been placed in the House Library.</p>
	<p pid="a.25.3/2">The work of the committee has already helped to inform the consultation paper we issued in May on future firearms controls and we will be considering its outstanding recommendations alongside other responses.</p>
</speech>
